  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor (Fire Protection)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Quantity Surveyor (Fire Protection)</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We are seeking a skilled Quantity Surveyor specializing in Fire Protection to join our team. The ideal candidate will assist in the preparation of tender submissions, manage cost estimation and measurement of quantities, and liaise with suppliers and contractors to evaluate proposals. The role requires timely preparation of Bills of Quantities, technical data, and unit rates while effectively communicating and collaborating with subcontractors, vendors, and suppliers.</p>\n<p>Responsibilities</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist in preparation of tender submission</li>\n  <li>Responsible for measurement of quantities &amp; cost estimation</li>\n  <li>Liaise with suppliers and contractors to get proposals/quotations and carry out evaluation</li>\n  <li>Timely preparation of Bills of Quantities, technical data &amp; unit rate</li>\n  <li>Liaise, communicate and work with subcontractors/vendors/suppliers</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Qualifications</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree/Diploma/NITEC and Higher NITEC in Mechanical Engineering</li>\n  <li>3-5 years QS experience related to FP services</li>\n  <li>MS Office software proficient</li>\n  <li>Cubic Cost Software proficient</li>\n  <li>A good team player</li>\n  <li>Highly self-motivated, good working attitude with high level of professionalism &amp; integrity</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>",
